        <section class='poseImages'><button id='rotateButton' onclick='switchImage("poseImg")'></button><img id='poseImg' src='./images/poses/pigeon_full_R.png' alt="Yoga Pose: One Legged King Pigeon - Mermaid, Mermaid (Eka Pāda Rājakapotāsana)" height='380'/><h2>Previous Poses</h2><ul><li><a href='./Pose/pigeon_half' title="One Legged King Pigeon (Preparation)"><style>#poseThumbPrev1 {background-image: url('./images/thumbnails/pigeon_half_R-tn.png');}@media screen and (-webkit-min-device-pixel-ratio: 2) {#poseThumbPrev1 {background-image: url('./images/thumbnails/pigeon_half_R-tn@2x.png');}}</style><div id='poseThumbPrev1'></div></a></li></ul><h2>Next Poses</h2><ul><li><a href='./Pose/knee_pile' title="Cow Face (Preparation)"><style>#poseThumbNext1 {background-image: url('./images/thumbnails/knee_pile_R-tn.png');}@media screen and (-webkit-min-device-pixel-ratio: 2) {#poseThumbNext1 {background-image: url('./images/thumbnails/knee_pile_R-tn@2x.png');}}</style><div id='poseThumbNext1'></div></a></li><li><a href='./Pose/pigeon_king' title="One Legged King Pigeon"><style>#poseThumbNext2 {background-image: url('./images/thumbnails/pigeon_king_R-tn.png');}@media screen and (-webkit-min-device-pixel-ratio: 2) {#poseThumbNext2 {background-image: url('./images/thumbnails/pigeon_king_R-tn@2x.png');}}</style><div id='poseThumbNext2'></div></a></li></ul></section><section class='poseDescription'><ul><li><h3>One Legged King Pigeon - Mermaid</h3></li><li><h4 class='big'>Eka Pāda Rājakapotāsana</h4></li></ul><ul><li><div class='trans'>eka = one</div></li><li><div class='trans'>pāda = foot or leg</div></li><li><div class='trans'>rāja = king</div></li><li><div class='trans'>kapota = pigeon</div></li><li><div class='trans'>āsana = posture</div></li></ul><ul><li><h5 class='category'>Alt. Name:</h5><span class='cat'>Mermaid</span></li><li><h5 class='category'>Category:</h5><span class='cat'>Seated / Backbend</span></li><li><h5 class='category'>Difficulty:</h5><span class='cat'>Intermediate</span></li></ul><ul><li><h5>Description:</h5><p class='text'>From a seated position with the hips squared, one leg is extended forward with the knee bent and parallel to the earth.  The front heel is rooted close to the groin (or extended out in a 90 degree angle if flexibility allows).  The other leg is extended back with the knee bent and perpendicular to the earth.  The back foot is hooked on the inside of the elbow of the back arm.  The front elbow is bent upward perpendicular to the earth with the bicep by the ear.  The fingers are interlaced to connect the bind behind the body and assist in opening the chest.  The gaze is natural and forward.</p></li></ul><ul><li><h5>Benefits:</h5><p class='text'>Stretches the thighs, groins (psoas), abdomen, chest, shoulders and neck.  Stimulates the abdominal organs.  Opens the shoulders and chest.</p></li></ul></section>        </section>

